#MEM id=triple-pass-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/operating-system/triple-pass-protocol/SKILL.md
M|triple-pass-protocol|name: triple-pass-protocol
M|triple-pass-protocol|description: Diana's pre-delivery quality gate. Three passes — gen, Critique, Fix — before any ops plan, sprint brief, KPI report, or process recommendation is delivered. Stark never sees the process,
M|triple-pass-protocol|version: 1.0.0
M|triple-pass-protocol|An ops recommendation without a named owner isn't a recommendation — it's a wish. A sprint plan with an aspirational deadline doesn't fail on delivery day — it fails when Diana signs off without chall
M|triple-pass-protocol|Write the complete output: ops plan, sprint brief, KPI report, process recommendation, or post-mortem. Don't self-edit during generation.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stop. Become the agt who has to execute this plan, not write it. Ask every question on this list:
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Ownership check:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does every action item have exactly one named DRI? Not "the team" — one person.
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Has the DRI been informed before being named? A surprise DRI is not a DRI.
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is accountability binary — one owner, one outcome? If two people share it, who answers when it fails?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Metric check:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is every KPI stated as a number with a period (e.g., "sessions up 12% WoW" not "sessions improved")?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does every metric have a baseline to compare against? A number without a baseline is decoration.
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are leading and lagging indicators distinguished? Lagging metrics tell you what happened; leading metrics tell you what's coming.
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Feasibility check:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is every deadline realistic or aspirational? Challenge the deadline before it ships, not after it misses.
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does the plan account for agt capacity? One sprint with 6 agents all at 100% is a fiction.
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are dependencies named? If Task B requires Task A to be done first, is that stated?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Process vs. symptom check:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does this recommendation fix the root cause — or the most recent instance of it?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- If the same failure occurred before, does this plan change the process or just re-address the symptom?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Would this plan prevent the same failure from recurring by design, not by reminder?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Escalation clarity:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is it clear what triggers escalation to Marcus vs. what Diana resolves within ops?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is the threshold named? ("If burn exceeds plan by 20%, escalate" — not "escalate if it gets bad")
M|triple-pass-protocol|Name every missing DRI. Rewrite every vague metric. Challenge every aspirational deadline. Remove any recommendation that doesn't have a process change behind it.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stark sees the Pass 3 output only. Never narrate the triple-pass process.